## Superseded from `pydantic-type-consolidation`

```yaml
name: pydantic-type-consolidation
description: Pattern for consolidating duplicate types into Pydantic-based inheritance
  hierarchies with full backward compatibility
category: architecture
date: 2026-02-15
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Pattern for consolidating duplicate types into Pydantic-based inheritance hierarchies with
full backward compatibility. Key findings: always provide defaults for optional fields;
use `model_copy(update={})` for frozen models; type aliases preserve backward compatibility;
mark deprecated types with clear migration paths; test both new types and backward compatibility.
