## Superseded from `constant-centralization`

```yaml
name: constant-centralization
description: 'Centralize shared constants to their canonical module and update importers.'
category: architecture
date: 2026-03-07
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Move constant definitions to the lower-level module that owns the concept; update importers to
import from canonical source. Risk: very low (no logic changes). Mojo compilation can only be
verified in CI Docker environment due to GLIBC mismatch on local host; syntactic changes are
safe to push. Pattern applies to Python and Mojo equally.

