## Superseded from `extract-detection-utils`

```yaml
name: extract-detection-utils
description: Pattern for extracting private detection/validation functions into centralized,
  reusable modules with optional caching
category: architecture
date: 2026-02-15
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Extract `_is_*()` / `_check_*()` functions into `<package>/<purpose>_detection.py` with
`@lru_cache(maxsize=128)`. `@lru_cache` and `unittest.mock.patch` conflict — use
`function.cache_clear()` or real filesystem via `tmp_path`. Don't manually remove imports;
let the linter handle it. Verified ProjectScylla PR #715 (Issue #647): 5 detection functions,
14 tests, 92.31% coverage, zero regressions.

