## Superseded from `orphan-module-subpackage-relocation`

```yaml
name: orphan-module-subpackage-relocation
description: Relocate an orphaned root-level module into the correct sub-package.
category: architecture
date: 2026-02-22
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
```

Prefer existing sub-package (KISS/YAGNI) over creating a new one. Copy file with zero content
changes — absolute imports work from any location. Use `git rm` (not plain `rm`) to preserve
history as rename (100% similarity detected automatically). Run 3-step smoke test: direct import,
re-export via `__init__`, CLI consumer. Verify zero dangling references.
Verified ProjectScylla Issue #847 / PR #958: 6 files changed, zero content changes in moved file.

