## Superseded from `odysseus-submodule-symlink-to-gitlink`

```yaml
name: odysseus-submodule-symlink-to-gitlink
description: "Convert absolute-path symlinks masquerading as git submodules into real git submodules."
category: architecture
date: 2026-03-29
version: "2.0.0"
user-invocable: false
verification: verified-local
```

Always `git rm` symlink first; confirm directory gone from disk before `git submodule add`.
Use full `https://github.com/OrgName/RepoName.git` absolute URLs in `.gitmodules` (not relative).
Verify exact org/repo casing on GitHub — case mismatch breaks CI clone.
Normalize `.gitmodules` to 4-space indentation. Verified Odysseus PR #66: 11 symlinks → 160000
gitlinks, all 14 submodule entries normalized.

