## Superseded from `clean-branches`

```yaml
name: clean-branches
description: Clean up stale git worktrees and merged/closed remote branches.
category: tooling
date: 2026-05-03
version: 1.1.0
user-invocable: false
```

PR merge status is the authoritative signal — use `gh pr list --head <branch> --state all`.
GitHub ruleset GH013 blocks `git push --delete` for >2 branches — use
`gh api -X DELETE "repos/{owner}/{repo}/git/refs/heads/<branch>"` loop instead.
`--force` cleanly removes worktrees with uncommitted changes (staged deletions, etc.).
Always enumerate remote refs via `gh api repos/.../git/refs/heads` (local `git branch -vv`
misses remote-only branches). Verified ProjectScylla: 59 branches deleted, GH013 bypass confirmed.
